{"id":"1104.4488","submitter":"Antonio Di Lorenzo","authors":"Antonio Di Lorenzo","title":"Hidden-variable models for the spin singlet. II. Local theories\n  violating Bell and Leggett inequalities","comments":"10 pages, no figures, comments welcome","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Three classes of local hidden-variable models that violate both Bell and\nLeggett inequalities are presented. The models, however, do not reproduce the\nquantum mechanical predictions, hence they are experimentally testable. It is\nconcluded that on one hand neither Bell or Leggett inequality fully captures\nthe essential counterintuitiveness of quantum mechanics, while on the other\nhand the hypothesis of outcome independence and that of locality are\nuncorrelated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Apr 2011 15:23:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-04-25"}
